{"title": "Permissive request parameters", "summary": "  Being overly permissive with request parameters can allow an attacker to update arbitrary model attributes. ", "description": "\n\nBeing overly permissive with request parameters can allow an attacker to\nupdate arbitrary model attributes.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid blanket permitting of parameters:\n\n```ruby\nparams.permit!\n```\n\n\u2705 Only permit parameters the user should be able to update:\n\n```ruby\nparams.permit(:name, :email)\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-913"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_rails_permissive_parameters"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}